00:02:44.640 --> 00:02:46.410
And now, it's my turn.

00:02:46.870 --> 00:02:49.060
So watch me, McQueen.

00:02:54.370 --> 00:02:55.500
Teio...

00:03:02.450 --> 00:03:05.820
When I go beyond giving 
everything I've got...

00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:11.540
I won't even reach the starting line 
unless I give everything I've got.

00:03:12.460 --> 00:03:13.440
But...

00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:18.400
Win the Arima Kinen!!

00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:15.850
I want to win!

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:21.150
It's that time once again.

00:03:21.150 --> 00:03:23.610
As the new year draws closer, 
here at the Nakayama Racecourse,

00:03:23.610 --> 00:03:25.620
a simmering intensity from 
the crowds and the track is

00:03:25.620 --> 00:03:27.530
enough to push back the seasonal cold.

00:03:27.530 --> 00:03:29.120
It's time for the G1 Arima Kinen!

00:03:29.120 --> 00:03:31.510
It certainly is. And with such 
a remarkable lineup this year,

00:03:31.510 --> 00:03:33.330
I think we're looking at an amazing race.

00:03:33.330 --> 00:03:38.970
Every year, the horse girls invited to run 
in this race are chosen by fan ballot.

00:03:36.130 --> 00:03:38.700
There's always something 
in the air during Arima...

00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:41.720
It really does feel like 
the year is wrapping up.

00:03:38.970 --> 00:03:42.880
And this year, we have eight remarkable 
contenders vying for this G1 title!

00:03:41.720 --> 00:03:42.880
Good point.

00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:46.390
There's no doubt in my mind that this will 
be a fitting race to conclude the year!

00:03:46.390 --> 00:03:48.010
Arima Kinen

00:03:46.670 --> 00:03:49.300
Who do you see winning this, Hosoe-san?

00:03:49.300 --> 00:03:51.200
I'm inclined to think it'll be
 a competitor from BNW

00:03:51.200 --> 00:03:52.680
who's here to represent 
the next generation.

00:03:52.680 --> 00:03:54.940
I think we can also look forward 
to seeing Mejiro Palmer

00:03:54.940 --> 00:03:58.040
continue her outrunning spree early on.

00:03:58.040 --> 00:04:01.780
Thanks for the input. Will we see a changing 
of the guard at this year's Arima Kinen?

00:04:01.780 --> 00:04:04.030
The horse girls will soon 
be taking to the track.

00:04:16.290 --> 00:04:18.070
Teio! You got a second?

00:04:18.070 --> 00:04:19.680
Oh, what's up?

00:04:21.710 --> 00:04:23.300
Prez?

00:04:21.710 --> 00:04:23.300
Thank you, Trainer.

00:04:23.300 --> 00:04:23.970
Don't mention it.

00:04:27.390 --> 00:04:30.080
You haven't worn that since the derby.

00:04:30.080 --> 00:04:32.980
Yeah. I wanted to run in this today.

00:04:32.980 --> 00:04:33.880
I see.

00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:41.180
Listen, can I ask you something weird?

00:04:42.040 --> 00:04:47.360
Did you ever do anything special when 
you wanted to win, no matter what?

00:04:51.710 --> 00:04:52.970
That's a tough one.

00:04:53.830 --> 00:04:57.590
Everyone who enters a race wants to win it.

00:04:58.330 --> 00:05:00.630
They've built themselves 
up in pursuit of victory...

00:05:00.630 --> 00:05:04.730
Gaining strength, focusing, 
all of it aimed toward competition.

00:05:05.860 --> 00:05:10.930
But in spite of that, no matter 
how good your condition is,

00:05:10.930 --> 00:05:12.740
there's always room for surprises.

00:05:12.740 --> 00:05:14.340
Anything can happen in a race.

00:05:15.790 --> 00:05:16.600
That said...

00:05:17.390 --> 00:05:22.150
If you have something you believe in, 
something that you will never yield on...

00:05:22.400 --> 00:05:25.010
That's one thing no one else can affect.

00:05:28.030 --> 00:05:30.540
Did that help at all?

00:05:28.030 --> 00:05:33.660
Tokai Teio

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:32.960
Yeah! Thanks, Prez.

00:05:33.950 --> 00:05:37.660
The horse girls are taking to 
the turf one after another.

00:05:37.660 --> 00:05:42.090
Is she a heel, or is she a hero? 
It's the blessing star, Rice Shower.

00:05:42.340 --> 00:05:43.970
She put on an amazing display when she upset

00:05:43.970 --> 00:05:46.090
Mejiro McQueen to take the Fall Tennoushou.

00:05:46.090 --> 00:05:50.270
I'm looking forward to the performance
 such a standout stayer puts on for us.

00:05:50.270 --> 00:05:55.100
And here we have the winner of last 
year's Arima Kinen, Mejiro Palmer!

00:05:55.100 --> 00:05:58.170
She's a first-rate outrunner horse girl.

00:05:58.170 --> 00:06:00.850
If she takes the lead early 
on and sets the pace,

00:06:00.850 --> 00:06:02.420
we could be looking at a consecutive win.

00:06:02.980 --> 00:06:05.050
Then there's Machikane Tannhäuser,

00:06:05.050 --> 00:06:07.670
who cuts an imposing figure when 
it comes to long distance races.

00:06:07.670 --> 00:06:10.270
Nice Nature will also be looking 
to relinquish her title of

00:06:10.270 --> 00:06:12.240
"Bronze Collector" to win this year's Arima.

00:06:12.240 --> 00:06:14.610
Nature-san seems to be in good shape.

00:06:14.610 --> 00:06:15.430
Right.

00:06:15.430 --> 00:06:17.700
I hope Tannhäuser-san can use the 
frustration over her last race

00:06:17.700 --> 00:06:19.420
to accomplish something this time around.

00:06:19.420 --> 00:06:21.540
I wanted to run in this!

00:06:21.540 --> 00:06:23.790
You should take that enthusiasm 
and put it into your cheering.

00:06:23.790 --> 00:06:25.880
Hey, is there any chance 
I could join in still?!

00:06:26.130 --> 00:06:27.190
No, there isn't.

00:06:27.190 --> 00:06:28.470
Fine...

00:06:29.010 --> 00:06:32.340
At the Japan Cup, she managed to outdo 
famous competitors from around the globe,

00:06:32.340 --> 00:06:34.820
scoring Relic Earth a significant victory.

00:06:34.820 --> 00:06:38.960
And across from her is one of the symbols 
of the next generation, Winning Ticket.

00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:41.590
All you need to say is that she's 
this year's Derby horse girl.

00:06:41.590 --> 00:06:43.270
I'm going to be paying attention to see

00:06:43.490 --> 00:06:44.910
if she lives up to those expectations.

00:06:44.910 --> 00:06:46.030
A good point.

00:06:47.150 --> 00:06:50.890
And here's Tokai Teio, returning to 
the turf after a year-long absence.

00:06:50.890 --> 00:06:54.660
Despite the long hiatus, she's the fourth 
most popular contender in the Arima Kinen!

00:06:54.660 --> 00:06:57.650
A lot of people have been 
waiting for her return.

00:06:57.650 --> 00:07:01.040
You can tell how strong the support 
for her is with that high ranking.

00:07:01.750 --> 00:07:03.050
Everybody looks so strong...

00:07:03.050 --> 00:07:04.650
You can't get intimidated, Kita-chan!

00:07:04.650 --> 00:07:07.730
Teio-san has to do a good job 
for McQueen-san's take, too!

00:07:07.730 --> 00:07:08.910
Y-You're right.

00:07:10.590 --> 00:07:13.010
And here we have today's 
star runner, Biwa Hayahide.

00:07:13.010 --> 00:07:15.680
One hundred percent of her races have 
had her in the top two!

00:07:15.680 --> 00:07:19.640
The undisputed most popular racer! Will she 
be able to live up to the fans' expectations?

00:07:19.640 --> 00:07:22.860
She's shown even greater 
development since summer.

00:07:22.860 --> 00:07:26.030
I think anyone looking to beat 
her will have their hands full.

00:07:28.400 --> 00:07:29.880
I'm back.

00:07:30.490 --> 00:07:31.460
Teio...

00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:33.820
Nature?

00:07:34.360 --> 00:07:36.180
I don't know what kind 
of condition you're in,

00:07:36.180 --> 00:07:38.540
and I don't care how you're going to run.

00:07:38.540 --> 00:07:43.170
All I care about is clearing the goal 
before you, and before anyone else.

00:07:43.560 --> 00:07:46.330
Yeah. I'm not losing to anyone else, either.

00:07:47.170 --> 00:07:48.740
Let's make this a good race.

00:07:49.640 --> 00:07:51.050
Oh, and...

00:07:51.910 --> 00:07:53.820
Welcome back, Teio.

00:07:56.050 --> 00:07:57.020
It's good to be back.

00:08:03.710 --> 00:08:05.380
You're out there watching, right?

00:08:05.940 --> 00:08:09.940
Umamusume

00:08:05.940 --> 00:08:09.940
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:08:20.350 --> 00:08:21.390
I'm frightened.

00:08:22.750 --> 00:08:24.450
Too frightened to watch...

00:08:26.200 --> 00:08:28.010
I want to believe in Teio.

00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:33.310
But... if she were to lose, I'd...

00:08:37.990 --> 00:08:40.220
The fanfare is now echoing 
throughout the stands.

00:08:40.220 --> 00:08:42.960
The Arima Kinen determines 
who ends the year on top...

00:08:42.960 --> 00:08:45.790
And the horse girls are 
entering their brackets.

00:08:45.790 --> 00:08:49.790
Each one of them is solemnly focused 
on living up to their fans' hopes,

00:08:49.790 --> 00:08:52.230
waiting for the moment that the gate opens.

00:08:52.230 --> 00:08:55.240
And on the far side gate, 
Mejiro Palmer is now in position.

00:08:55.240 --> 00:08:58.080
All fourteen competitors 
are now in their brackets.

00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:00.240
It's the last G1 race of the year,
the Arima Kinen!

00:09:00.880 --> 00:09:02.420
And they're off!

00:09:02.420 --> 00:09:05.250
Mejiro Palmer is out in front,
 with a good start!

00:09:05.250 --> 00:09:07.530
These horse girls all seem 
to have made a smooth start!

00:09:07.530 --> 00:09:10.270
You can see why these fourteen were selected!
 A fine group of competitors!

00:09:10.270 --> 00:09:12.030
Teio's running...

00:09:12.030 --> 00:09:12.750
Yeah.

00:09:12.750 --> 00:09:13.860
Teio...

00:09:13.860 --> 00:09:15.380
I'm glad I got to see this.

00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:17.990
Who from BNW is gonna win today?

00:09:17.990 --> 00:09:19.390
Probably Biwa Hayahide.

00:09:21.140 --> 00:09:24.500
The last time Tokai Teio raced 
was last year's Arima Kinen...

00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:27.950
It's been 364 days since then. 
Her return came after a long blank.

00:09:27.950 --> 00:09:28.770
What's brought that on?

00:09:28.770 --> 00:09:31.620
There's never been a single horse girl

00:09:31.620 --> 00:09:33.280
that has won a G1 race 
after such a long hiatus!

00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:34.570
Do you think she can pull it off?

00:09:34.570 --> 00:09:37.390
You're really gonna ask that? 
She came in 11th last year.

00:09:37.390 --> 00:09:38.190
My bad.

00:09:38.190 --> 00:09:40.030
Of course it'll be hard!

00:09:40.030 --> 00:09:42.410
But Teio-san's still running!

00:09:42.410 --> 00:09:43.990
She's right!

00:09:43.990 --> 00:09:44.940
Yep.

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:51.090
There really is nothing like a real race!

00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:54.210
I can feel them around me... 
feel how much they want to win...

00:09:54.210 --> 00:09:56.150
I can sense all kinds of stuff!

00:09:56.150 --> 00:09:58.780
I wanted to get a bigger lead, 
but they're right on my tail!

00:09:58.780 --> 00:10:01.180
But my legs are still good to go!

00:10:01.180 --> 00:10:04.200
I might've given up the Kikkashou, 
but this time I'm winning!

00:10:04.200 --> 00:10:06.940
I'll win this race, 
and win cheers and adulation!

00:10:06.940 --> 00:10:08.040
I don't wanna lose!

00:10:08.040 --> 00:10:11.690
I have to cross the goal in first place, 
not second, and definitely not third!

00:10:11.690 --> 00:10:14.190
I can be the star, too!

00:10:14.610 --> 00:10:16.720
Coming around the fourth corner,
they're in front of the stands.

00:10:15.940 --> 00:10:19.570
But... I can't lose! I won't lose!

00:10:16.720 --> 00:10:19.570
These fourteen elite racers are bathed 
in cheers as they make their way onward.

00:10:19.570 --> 00:10:21.470
Mejiro Palmer is still in the lead.

00:10:21.470 --> 00:10:23.130
Biwa Hayahide is currently in fourth place,

00:10:23.130 --> 00:10:24.860
with Rice Shower moving up on the outside.

00:10:24.860 --> 00:10:27.340
Tokai Teio seems to be a 
bit further to the back.

00:10:27.340 --> 00:10:30.330
One has to wonder how she's feeling, 
running after an entire year.

00:10:28.290 --> 00:10:29.300
Teio...

00:10:30.330 --> 00:10:32.830
Come on! You can do this, Teio!

00:10:32.830 --> 00:10:34.510
I wonder how she's doing?

00:10:34.510 --> 00:10:37.180
She tended to drift a little 
to the right during practice.

00:10:37.180 --> 00:10:39.690
You saw how much she trained! She'll be fine!

00:10:39.690 --> 00:10:42.590
She didn't manage to get back to 
where she used to be in time.

00:10:42.590 --> 00:10:48.530
But we'll still be cheering for 
you until the very end, Teio!

00:10:48.530 --> 00:10:51.920
The horse girls are now entering 
the home stretch of the first lap.

00:10:51.920 --> 00:10:55.730
The chosen 14 are running in front 
of the entire Nakayama crowd.

00:10:53.870 --> 00:10:55.730
Tokai Teio-san...

00:10:55.730 --> 00:10:57.730
Tokai Teio can't win?!

00:10:57.950 --> 00:11:01.860
The hell are you saying, boss?! 
Look at how hard she's trying!

00:11:01.860 --> 00:11:04.110
Anybody can try hard.

00:11:04.110 --> 00:11:06.690
If that's all it took to win, life'd be easy.

00:11:06.690 --> 00:11:10.500
If Teio pulls this off, I'll shave my head.

00:11:10.500 --> 00:11:14.000
The 14 racers are now coming around the 
second corner and entering the backstretch!

00:11:14.220 --> 00:11:16.500
Let's check their position.

00:11:16.500 --> 00:11:20.510
Mejiro Palmer in the lead, with Vice Stone 
in second, and Relic Earth in third.

00:11:20.510 --> 00:11:24.640
Biwa Hayahide is in fourth, and behind 
her are Winning Ticket and Rice Shower.

00:11:24.640 --> 00:11:27.080
The returning Tokai Teio followed by Pella,

00:11:27.080 --> 00:11:31.060
Ferment Win, Nice Nature, 
Duo Priwen, Spur Mover,

00:11:31.060 --> 00:11:35.020
Avec Dream, and Machikane 
Tannhäuser at the moment!

00:11:35.020 --> 00:11:39.970
As expected, the early lead is going 
to the Mejiro clan's star outrunner,

00:11:39.970 --> 00:11:41.400
Mejiro Palmer.

00:11:41.400 --> 00:11:46.030
That's true. But this year, all thirteen 
of her competitors are within ten lengths.

00:11:46.950 --> 00:11:50.040
There's still no telling who 
could move up in position.

00:11:50.790 --> 00:11:53.080
So watch me, McQueen.

00:11:53.390 --> 00:11:56.670
She managed to outrun the competition to 
the end during last year's Arima Kinen.

00:11:56.670 --> 00:11:58.700
It's now a question of who's 
going to take action,

00:11:58.700 --> 00:12:00.880
as they begin to enter the third corner.

00:12:00.880 --> 00:12:02.300
I'm gonna win!

00:12:02.300 --> 00:12:03.680
I'm going to win!

00:12:03.670 --> 00:12:04.930
I'm gonna win!

00:12:04.930 --> 00:12:06.180
I'm gonna win!

00:12:06.180 --> 00:12:07.680
I'm gonna win!

00:12:08.700 --> 00:12:11.180
I have to... I have to!

00:12:11.180 --> 00:12:13.710
The racers are making their 
way into the fourth corner.

00:12:13.710 --> 00:12:16.750
Biwa Hayahide and Winning Ticket 
are steadily moving up...

00:12:16.750 --> 00:12:18.440
Is Relic Earth making her move?

00:12:18.440 --> 00:12:21.900
Whoa! And it looks like Biwa 
Hayahide is taking off!

00:12:21.900 --> 00:12:25.700
The winner of the Kikkashou, Biwa Hayahide, 
is making her way forward in the ranks!

00:12:25.700 --> 00:12:29.670
Mejiro Palmer is passed! Biwa Hayahide 
is now in the lead! She's in first!

00:12:29.670 --> 00:12:32.190
Biwa Hayahide is strong enough 
to justify her popularity!

00:12:32.190 --> 00:12:34.920
Is there any horse girl here 
who can keep up with her?!

00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:37.340
Will it be Rice Shower? Nice Nature?

00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:39.070
What about Winning Ticket?!

00:12:39.070 --> 00:12:40.800
You're not getting away from me!

00:13:15.160 --> 00:13:16.980
Tokai Teio is closing in!

00:13:16.980 --> 00:13:19.420
Wait... Tokai Teio is closing in?!

00:13:58.670 --> 00:14:00.670
My lungs hurt.

00:14:00.670 --> 00:14:02.670
But I don't care if they burst!

00:14:03.180 --> 00:14:06.380
My legs are so heavy. 
But they're still moving!

00:14:07.060 --> 00:14:10.220
I lost my way so many times!

00:14:10.920 --> 00:14:13.220
Back then... And then...

00:14:13.620 --> 00:14:15.720
More than anyone else!

00:14:16.100 --> 00:14:19.220
I've felt frustrated more than anyone else!

00:14:19.730 --> 00:14:22.880
And I want to win more than anyone else!

00:14:23.610 --> 00:14:28.980
So I'm not letting you win! 
No matter what... No matter what!

00:14:29.980 --> 00:14:33.720
No matter what, I'm winning!

00:14:39.540 --> 00:14:40.500
Go...

00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:41.500
Go!

00:14:41.500 --> 00:14:44.000
Go! Run!

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:47.660
Let's do this!

00:14:48.010 --> 00:14:50.960
It's Tokai Teio! Tokai Teio is moving up!

00:14:50.960 --> 00:14:53.080
She's closing in on Biwa Hayahide's lead!

00:14:53.080 --> 00:14:56.510
There's 200 meters left! Tokai Teio 
hasn't been on the track in a year!

00:14:56.730 --> 00:14:59.020
Will she be able to catch 
up to Biwa Hayahide?!

00:14:59.020 --> 00:15:01.400
She's giving everything she has to move up!

00:15:02.080 --> 00:15:04.220
Teio-san!

00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:05.350
Teio!

00:15:05.760 --> 00:15:08.780
Tokai Teio chases! 
But Biwa Hayahide won't be caught!

00:15:08.780 --> 00:15:09.710
One length between them!

00:15:08.780 --> 00:15:10.030
Go!

00:15:09.710 --> 00:15:12.780
But that last gap doesn't seem 
to shrink for Tokai Teio!

00:15:12.780 --> 00:15:14.720
Biwa Hayahide isn't budging!

00:15:14.720 --> 00:15:17.380
She's demonstrating the strength 
that set a <i>record at the Kikkashou!</i>

00:15:16.530 --> 00:15:17.790
Go!

00:15:17.380 --> 00:15:18.910
She won't let Tokai Teio pass!

00:15:17.790 --> 00:15:18.910
Go for it!

00:15:18.910 --> 00:15:20.910
But Tokai Teio is still closing in!

00:15:20.910 --> 00:15:22.420
Go!

00:15:20.910 --> 00:15:24.430
Having returned to the track, 
</i>Teio slowly crosses the gap!

00:15:24.430 --> 00:15:27.280
There's 100 meters in the race!
 Only 100 meters to go!

00:15:24.670 --> 00:15:25.920
Go!

00:15:25.920 --> 00:15:26.920
Go!

00:15:26.920 --> 00:15:29.420
Go... Go!

00:15:27.280 --> 00:15:30.670
This is the last battle! Will Tokai Teio 
be able to catch up to Biwa Hayahide?!

00:15:30.670 --> 00:15:34.270
Will it be the symbol of the new generation, 
Biwa Hayahide, or the revived Tokai Teio?!

00:15:34.270 --> 00:15:36.930
Nakayama... Nakayama is 
shaking for the Arima Kinen!

00:15:36.930 --> 00:15:38.930
Which of these two will seize victory?!

00:15:44.420 --> 00:15:47.130
It's Tokai Teio! Tokai Teio passes her!

00:15:47.130 --> 00:15:48.910
Tokai Teio takes a slight lead!

00:15:48.320 --> 00:15:49.940
Go!

00:15:48.910 --> 00:15:52.110
But it's a narrow one! <i>Biwa Hayahide 
will be looking to catch up!</i>

00:15:49.940 --> 00:15:51.320
Go!

00:15:51.320 --> 00:15:52.700
Go!

00:15:52.110 --> 00:15:54.200
Is it going to be Tokai Teio
 or Biwa Hayahide?!

00:15:52.700 --> 00:15:54.200
Go!

00:15:54.200 --> 00:15:57.700
Tokai Teio and Biwa Hayahide! 
Tokai Teio! Biwa Hayahide!

00:15:57.700 --> 00:16:00.200
Will the Derby winner hold strong?!

00:16:00.650 --> 00:16:03.730
Tokai Teio! Tokai Teio is in the lead!

00:16:03.730 --> 00:16:07.400
Tokai Teio makes a miraculous return!

00:16:15.810 --> 00:16:16.710
I did it.

00:16:19.930 --> 00:16:21.820
After an entire year...

00:16:22.350 --> 00:16:24.990
Tokai Teio has managed to win 
this race. It's a miracle.

00:16:24.990 --> 00:16:29.140
She has demonstrated nothing 
less than a miracle on this day!

00:16:29.140 --> 00:16:31.300
Who could have imagined it?!

00:16:31.300 --> 00:16:36.110
For the first time since last year's 
Arima Kinen, Tokai Teio has raced...

00:16:36.110 --> 00:16:38.120
And she has managed to defeat 
thirteen other challengers!

00:16:38.530 --> 00:16:41.120
Hosoe-san, this has been a huge shock!

00:16:39.620 --> 00:16:41.120
Arima Kinen

00:16:41.120 --> 00:16:43.910
I can't believe what I just saw. 
We're looking at a historic moment.

00:16:43.910 --> 00:16:45.120
I have to agree.

00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:47.970
Winning a G1 race after such 
a significant hiatus...

00:16:47.970 --> 00:16:50.670
It's something that's never been done before!

00:16:50.670 --> 00:16:53.990
Three fractures </i>left doubt 
if she'd ever run again,

00:16:53.990 --> 00:16:56.380
and after being told she was done for,

00:16:56.380 --> 00:17:01.090
Tokai Teio has grasped a historic 
victory through an indomitable spirit!

00:17:01.090 --> 00:17:02.980
It was truly a remarkable win,

00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:06.070
against an incredible G1 lineup, 
after such a long time.

00:17:06.070 --> 00:17:09.500
This was a race that defied the 
expectations of the Twinkle Series.

00:17:09.500 --> 00:17:13.110
Biwa Hayahide seemed to have things wrapped 
up entering the final straightaway,

00:17:13.110 --> 00:17:17.750
but Tokai Teio's almost obsessive acceleration 
forced her into second place.

00:17:16.820 --> 00:17:21.830
Nakayama

00:17:16.820 --> 00:17:21.830
Results

00:17:16.820 --> 00:17:21.830
{\an1}Turf: Good
Time:

00:17:17.750 --> 00:17:20.550
There was a lineup of horse girls today 
where any one of them could have won,

00:17:20.550 --> 00:17:24.030
but in the end, Tokai Teio's dedication 
is what let her come out on top.

00:17:24.030 --> 00:17:25.920
Nice Nature put on an admirable performance,

00:17:25.180 --> 00:17:48.140
Teio! Teio! Teio!

00:17:25.920 --> 00:17:28.500
but will sadly have to settle 
for third place again this year.

00:17:28.500 --> 00:17:31.840
Oh, and there's a Teio chant!

00:17:31.840 --> 00:17:34.370
The same one heard on the 
day of the Japan Derby!

00:17:34.370 --> 00:17:37.380
No, I think it might be even louder!

00:17:37.380 --> 00:17:39.680
It echoes throughout the Nakayama Racecourse!

00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:42.340
Tokai Teio has dazzled 
all of these fans today!

00:17:42.340 --> 00:17:46.600
Overturning all expectations and casting 
the very notion of submission aside,

00:17:46.600 --> 00:17:51.540
she has given rise to a new 
legend in the Arima Kinen!

00:17:48.170 --> 00:17:49.770
Teio...

00:17:50.030 --> 00:17:52.650
Teio might have just outdone the Emperor!

00:17:52.650 --> 00:17:55.280
I guess prodigies really do exist, 
as frustrating as that might be!

00:17:52.650 --> 00:18:11.020
Teio! Teio! Teio!

00:17:55.960 --> 00:17:57.300
Thanks, guys.

00:17:57.300 --> 00:17:59.700
You... holy... Tei...

00:17:59.700 --> 00:18:01.740
We can't even tell what you're saying!

00:18:01.740 --> 00:18:03.100
You did it, Teio!

00:18:03.100 --> 00:18:06.050
Teio-san, congratulations!

00:18:06.050 --> 00:18:08.870
Suzuka-san is happy, too!

00:18:08.870 --> 00:18:10.190
Yeah. Thanks.

00:18:10.190 --> 00:18:11.670
Huh? She's not answering?

00:18:11.670 --> 00:18:13.750
It really was a wonderful race.

00:18:14.170 --> 00:18:15.920
Congratulations, Teio.

00:18:15.920 --> 00:18:17.770
Suzuka-san?! Why?!

00:18:17.770 --> 00:18:20.420
I wanted to cheer her on 
in person, so I flew in.

00:18:20.420 --> 00:18:22.680
Suzuka-san!

00:18:22.680 --> 00:18:25.830
You should've told me you were coming!

00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:31.480
Did you see that?

00:18:31.970 --> 00:18:34.510
Yes... I did.

00:18:36.190 --> 00:18:38.820
Thank you, Teio!

00:18:39.480 --> 00:18:40.450
McQueen—

00:18:43.070 --> 00:18:45.500
What!? What is all this?!

00:18:45.500 --> 00:18:48.580
Hey, you guys are kinda heavy!

00:18:51.580 --> 00:18:52.980
Congratulations, Teio!

00:18:52.980 --> 00:18:54.350
Congratulations!

00:18:55.960 --> 00:18:57.700
Congratulations.

00:18:58.500 --> 00:19:00.140
Thanks, Rice.

00:19:18.910 --> 00:19:21.170
I wanna run to a dream with you,

00:19:21.170 --> 00:19:28.540
over and over, until we see 
what's beyond victory!

00:19:38.690 --> 00:19:41.260
We're young, so let's have a good time

00:19:41.260 --> 00:19:46.890
No matter how tough it gets, if you enjoy yourself,
 the crowds will cheer you on!

00:19:46.890 --> 00:19:48.680
Full points for spirit!

00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:53.370
I think if I was on my own, 
I never would've realized

00:19:53.370 --> 00:19:57.560
There's no room for "impossible" 
in my dictionary!

00:19:57.560 --> 00:19:59.900
Just like a puzzle,

00:19:59.900 --> 00:20:03.280
you have the future, now, and yesterday!

00:20:03.280 --> 00:20:04.230
No more!

00:20:04.230 --> 00:20:06.020
Not gonna lose our way!

00:20:06.020 --> 00:20:06.740
Let's go!

00:20:06.740 --> 00:20:09.160
And we're never gonna stop!

00:20:09.400 --> 00:20:11.750
I wanna run to a dream with you,

00:20:11.750 --> 00:20:14.520
pushing each other to always get better!

00:20:14.520 --> 00:20:16.330
With endless power, I can be!

00:20:16.330 --> 00:20:20.170
And even if I fall, I'll get up once again!

00:20:20.170 --> 00:20:22.500
Try! Always at full power!

00:20:22.500 --> 00:20:25.430
The future all depends on you!

00:20:25.430 --> 00:20:27.550
We'll zip right past expectations

00:20:27.550 --> 00:20:33.730
Leaving them behind and making 
an unforgettable miracle real!

00:20:33.730 --> 00:20:34.350
Come on!

00:20:34.350 --> 00:20:36.100
We're sharing the same dream!

00:20:36.100 --> 00:20:36.800
Come on!

00:20:36.800 --> 00:20:38.670
The sun is high in my heart!

00:20:39.270 --> 00:20:40.070
And you better never forget!

00:20:40.070 --> 00:20:42.320
I wanna run to a dream with you,

00:20:42.320 --> 00:20:46.380
where our hopes will always be waiting!

00:20:50.830 --> 00:20:52.300
I'll be up there one day.

00:21:08.290 --> 00:21:11.760
This is why I told you to go to 
bed early before important days!

00:21:11.760 --> 00:21:15.520
I mean, come on! I was too 
nervous to sleep, anyway!

00:21:15.520 --> 00:21:18.520
En<font color="#464742">trance Ceremony</font>

00:21:18.520 --> 00:21:22.530
Entrance
Ceremony

00:21:27.010 --> 00:21:28.970
We're finally here, Dia-chan.

00:21:28.970 --> 00:21:31.500
Yeah. Let's work hard together, Kita-chan.

00:21:40.390 --> 00:21:41.960
I apologize for the wait.

00:21:46.550 --> 00:21:48.620
Nah. No apologies necessary.

00:21:49.430 --> 00:21:51.270
We can finally race each other.

00:21:51.680 --> 00:21:52.480
Yes.

00:21:53.800 --> 00:21:58.840
Two thousand and four hundred meters on turf.
 Clear weather. Track condition, good.

00:21:59.690 --> 00:22:02.070
Just don't cry if you lose, okay?

00:22:02.070 --> 00:22:04.820
You're up against the strongest 
horse girl, after all.

00:22:04.820 --> 00:22:06.940
I wouldn't have it any other way.

